  "content": "\u003cp\u003eI think many people are forgetting the complete picture with gRPC. Everything pitched as an alternatives are lacking performance or message size or some other aspect. It\u0026#39;s either that or the suggestion just covers one aspect of gRPC, like an alternative to protobuf encoding or something without a schema intended to be shared.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI really do feel like gRPC strikes a really special balance of type safety, performance and unique features like the ability to handle client, server and bidi streaming and the amount of languages that support protobuf now is really great.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eNow is the time to re-imagine client support in each language and trim off the features turned out to be un-needed. ConnectRPC, for example, has done a great job of this.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://infosec.exchange/tags/protobuf\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\"\u003e#\u003cspan\u003eprotobuf\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://infosec.exchange/tags/grpc\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\"\u003e#\u003cspan\u003egrpc\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
